<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1812,2019]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1812,1838]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
1) body orange, except the head, hind leg (proximal part of coxa orange), and tergites VI+ black; 2) fore wing blackish, with the yellowish hyaline band between the junction of vein 
<emphasis box="[1083,1117,1849,1875]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">RA</emphasis>
up to pterostigma until half vein 
<emphasis box="[206,229,1885,1910]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">M</emphasis>
, pterostigma black; 3) head, in dorsal view, with gena slightly convex behind eyes; 4) face sculptured below the insertion of antennae, with longitudinal carina in the middle region; 5) occipital carina projected, not curved upwards, with a concavity in the apex dorsally; 6) pronotum with the pocket-like structure reduced longitudinally; 7) epicnemial carina absent; 8) sternite I with a ventral projection, spine-like, posteriorly; 9) female with tarsal claw with more or less square lobe, and with apex overtaking the lobe (tarsal claw single in males); 10) female with ovipositor sheath about 1.0 × as long as the hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,1318,222,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,222,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,427,223,249]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[482,537,223,249]" name="Peru" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Peru</collectingCountry>
. This is the first record of the species and genus for 
<collectingCountry box="[1120,1202,223,249]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1218,1305,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[166,1421,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Geographical distribution of the Hymenoepimecis species. (A) H. atlantica sp. n.; (B) H. castilloi Pádua &amp; Sääksjärvi, 2020; (C) Hymenoepimecis japi Sobczak, Loffredo, Penteado-Dias &amp; Gonzaga, 2009; (D) H. ribeiroi Pádua &amp; Sobczak, 2015; (E) H. uberensis Pádua &amp; Onody, 2015; (F) H. veranii Loffredo &amp; Penteado-Dias, 2009." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911289/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
